The Nigerian Army has released the list of successful candidates for its 80 Regular Recruit Intake (RRI). It also announced that the screening would commence on December 2. The Army disclosed this in a post via its Twitter handle on Tuesday morning. It also advised candidates to visit the Nigerian Army official website for more information. “This is to inform the general public that the list of shortlisted candidates for 80RRI has been released and screening will commence on December 2, 2020,” it said. <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone size-full wp-image-857132" src="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/army.jpg" alt="" width="573" height="402" srcset="https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/army.jpg 573w, https://dailypost.ng/wp-content/uploads/2020/12/army-300x210.jpg 300w" sizes="(max-width: 573px) 100vw, 573px">